<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Another public appearance demanded another stylish outfit as Kelly Brook left her day job at Global Radio Studios on Wednesday.</p>

<p>The presenter caught the eye as she made her way across London's Leicester Square in a tasteful white blouse and skinny black jeans. </p>

<p>Kelly, who co-hosts the Heart London Drive Show with Jason King, added to her look with a pair of smart knee-length leather boots. </p>

<p>Looking good: Another public appearance demanded another stylish outfit as Kelly Brook left her day job at Global Radio Studios on Wednesday</p>

<p>Accessorizing tastefully, the brunette carried a small black handbag in one hand as she prepare for the journey home. </p>

<p>Rich make-up drew further attention to her instantly recognisable features, while distinctive tinted sunglasses rounded things off. </p>

<p>Evidently in high spirits, Kelly gave onlookers a beaming smile during her latest outing in the capital.  </p>

<p>Stylish: The presenter caught the eye as she made her way across London's Leicester Square in a tasteful white blouse and skinny black jeans</p>

<p>Nice touch: Accessorizing tastefully, the brunette carried a small black handbag in one hand as she prepare for the journey home</p>

<p>Kelly's casual display comes as she admitted she's 'not worried' about her 'weight creeping up'.</p>

<p>She also declared 'diets shouldn't be about deprivation', after revealing she shed a whopping two stone in March.</p>

<p>While she has been keeping busy by exercising at home, her diet consists of 'healthy, low-calorie meals' with sweet treats such as popcorn and homemade fruit lollies.</p>

<p>Hard to miss: Rich make-up drew further attention to her instantly recognisable features, while distinctive tinted sunglasses rounded things off</p>

<p>The brunette has been candid about her weight fluctuating, with the bombshell slimming down to a size 10-12 after going to a size 16.</p>

<p>On her current figure, she told new! magazine: 'I'm a real foodie and enjoy cooking. I wasn't surprised at all to see my weight creep up a little over the last few weeks.</p>

<p>'[I've gained] a few pounds, but I'm not worried. I know I can lean on the SlimFast 3.2.1. Plan to deal with my weight loss ups and downs, so I can get back on track.</p>

<p>'It's easy and it works. Diets shouldn't be about deprivation - they need to be sustainable after all.'</p>
